Description: Rim and wall sherd of East Greek pottery bowl; grooved horizontal ledge rim; interior and top of rim glazed; exterior reserved, with graffito.
Curator's comments: For the reserved exterior compare 1924,1201.896 from the lower parts of a (different) bowl.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.089)
